comments: One of the best teachers! I really did learn a lot from her Comm class.

A GREAT CLASS WITH A GREAT INSTRUCTOR. THE QUALITY OVERALL IS GOOD. I could care less what she looks like or that she used to work for MTV, or whether she is a young instructor. Unfortunately The Deadlines for outlines are strict! No late outlines are accepted meaning you arent allowed to do your speech. That hurts ur grade Practical class but hard

Good class but Mrs. Payne does not explain projects well. Make sure to ask a lot of questions because her instructions are very broad and you most likely get comments like "you should have" or "I wish you would have." When extra credit it given DO IT it ends up counting against you if you don\'t. But over all a good class.
Very informative class! Mrs. Payne is extremely helpful and explains everything very well. Although her explaining things can take a little longer then needed you will always learn something.
Janelle is extremely positive and helpful! At first, many people were nervous about the speeches. By the end, everyone knew each other well and improved!

Mrs Payne is a great teacher! She is helpful, kind, and she explans things in a way that is easy to understand. Tests are easy, just read the chapter right before each 5 question, multiple choice test. Activities are simple, fun, and informative. Mrs Payne is one of the best teachers at West Valley, and the best Communication teacher on campus!

Janelle is probably one of the best teachers at WVC. She forces you to get to know your peers around you so that when you make a speech you make it to friends and not just classmates. I love how she clearly explains what needs to be done and always gives positive feedback. If she every has an avaliable class, be sure to take her cuz she is awesome

The class itself was fun because everyone got to know each other very well in the end. The material was a bit challenging because it really depends on how determined you are to do well on your speeches. Make sure to do the reading to ace those short quizzes, they add up. If you\'re disciplined enough you can easily get an A.

took her interpersonal communication class. thought it would be sort of a skate through class but i actually learned a lot. if you show up every day(which isnt tough because shes very attractive) you\'ll do well. take it and improve your interpersonal skills

I just finished a winter session of public speaking with Mrs Payne and I have to admit that I enjoyed the class! And I don\'t like public speaking but she made it so much easier and relaxing. She has a great teaching style and if you are nervous I highly recommend taking her class, she is supportive and probably one of the best teachers I\'ve had!
